  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrently, ArC's `InstanceHandle` always contains a fully constructed instance of the bean. I propose that it should become lazy (that is, resolve the contextual reference on the first call to `get`), because:\r\n\r\n- Weld's `WeldInstance.Handler` is lazy;\r\n- upcoming CDI 4.0 `Instance.Handle` is lazy;\r\n- ArC's `InstanceHandle` is very close to both of them.\r\n\r\nGranted, those are not terribly strong arguments, so this certainly isn't high priority.\r\n\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
